bead.description:
Migrate the UI from the legacy X-Axon-Database header to ADR-018 path-based routing. The existing UI has a tenant picker (in stores.svelte.ts + a TenantSelector component) that sets the db_name slug on every request. This bead adds a database picker within the tenant, prepends /tenants/:t/databases/:d/ to every API URL, and drops the X-Axon-Database header.

## Scope

### 1. Extend the selection store

File: ui/src/lib/stores.svelte.ts (currently 25 lines)

Add alongside the existing selectedTenant:

    let selectedDatabase: TenantDatabase | null = $state(null);

    export function getSelectedDatabase(): TenantDatabase | null {
      return selectedDatabase;
    }

    export function setSelectedDatabase(db: TenantDatabase | null): void {
      selectedDatabase = db;
    }

Add a TenantDatabase type in ui/src/lib/api.ts that mirrors the server:
    export type TenantDatabase = {
      tenant_id: string;
      name: string;
      created_at_ms: number;
    };

### 2. Rewrite the request helper in ui/src/lib/api.ts

Currently:
    async function request<T>(path: string, init?: RequestInit, dbName?: string | null): Promise<T> {
      const headers = new Headers(init?.headers);
      if (init?.body && !headers.has('Content-Type')) {
        headers.set('Content-Type', 'application/json');
      }
      if (dbName) {
        headers.set('X-Axon-Database', dbName);
      }
      const response = await fetch(path, { ...init, headers });
      ...
    }

Change to:

    type Scope = { tenant: string; database: string } | null;

    async function request<T>(path: string, init?: RequestInit, scope?: Scope): Promise<T> {
      const headers = new Headers(init?.headers);
      if (init?.body && !headers.has('Content-Type')) {
        headers.set('Content-Type', 'application/json');
      }

      // Control-plane routes (/control/*) are NOT tenant-scoped.
      const url = scope && !path.startsWith('/control/')
        ? `/tenants/${encodeURIComponent(scope.tenant)}/databases/${encodeURIComponent(scope.database)}${path}`
        : path;

      const response = await fetch(url, { ...init, headers });
      ...
    }

Remove the X-Axon-Database header set entirely.

### 3. Update every exported function signature

Every exported function in api.ts that currently takes `dbName?: string | null` should take `scope?: Scope` instead. That's ~20 functions. Grep for `dbName` in api.ts and update each one.

The fetchTenants / createTenant / deleteTenant control-plane functions do NOT take a scope because /control/tenants is not tenant-scoped.

### 4. Update call sites in routes

ui/src/routes/schemas/+page.svelte, audit/+page.svelte, collections/+page.svelte, collections/[name]/+page.svelte — wherever they call `getSelectedTenant()?.db_name`, replace with a scope builder:

    import { getSelectedTenant, getSelectedDatabase } from '$lib/stores.svelte';

    function currentScope(): Scope {
      const t = getSelectedTenant();
      const d = getSelectedDatabase();
      if (!t || !d) return null;
      return { tenant: t.name, database: d.name };  // Note: `name` not `db_name`
    }

Pass `currentScope()` everywhere `getSelectedTenant()?.db_name` used to be.

Caveat: the existing tenants.name uses the legacy slug (db_name) because control_plane.rs (which C1/C2 did NOT touch) still returns that shape. For this bead, accept that the UI passes `t.name` (the new display name) OR `t.db_name` (the legacy slug). Since C1/C2 left legacy tenant CRUD alone, the existing /control/tenants GET returns `db_name` on the tenant row. Use `t.db_name` as the `tenant` value for path URLs until legacy tenants are migrated.

OR: use --no-auth mode's path semantics (from E2) — any URL works, the backend synthesizes a namespace. For the UI in dev mode, call `{ tenant: "default", database: "default" }` when no explicit selection is made. That's simpler and matches bootstrap semantics.

Recommendation: default scope is `{ tenant: "default", database: "default" }` when no selection. When the user picks a tenant from the dropdown, use `t.db_name` (legacy slug) as both the tenant and database path segments for now. This keeps the UI functional against the existing server, and the cleanup comes when legacy tenants are fully migrated.

### 5. Database selector component

Create ui/src/lib/DatabaseSelector.svelte:

    <script lang="ts">
      import { getSelectedTenant, getSelectedDatabase, setSelectedDatabase } from '$lib/stores.svelte';
      import { fetchTenantDatabases, type TenantDatabase } from '$lib/api';

      let databases = $state<TenantDatabase[]>([]);
      let loading = $state(false);

      $effect(() => {
        const tenant = getSelectedTenant();
        if (!tenant) {
          databases = [];
          return;
        }
        loading = true;
        fetchTenantDatabases(tenant.id).then(dbs => {
          databases = dbs;
          loading = false;
          // Auto-select the first database if none selected.
          if (!getSelectedDatabase() && dbs.length > 0) {
            setSelectedDatabase(dbs[0]);
          }
        });
      });
    </script>

    <select
      value={getSelectedDatabase()?.name ?? ''}
      onchange={(e) => {
        const name = (e.target as HTMLSelectElement).value;
        const db = databases.find(d => d.name === name) ?? null;
        setSelectedDatabase(db);
      }}
    >
      {#each databases as db}
        <option value={db.name}>{db.name}</option>
      {/each}
    </select>

Add fetchTenantDatabases to api.ts:

    export async function fetchTenantDatabases(tenantId: string): Promise<TenantDatabase[]> {
      const response = await request<{ databases: TenantDatabase[] }>(
        `/control/tenants/${encodeURIComponent(tenantId)}/databases`,
      );
      return response.databases;
    }

### 6. Wire DatabaseSelector into the header

Find where TenantSelector (if it exists — check ui/src/lib or ui/src/routes/+layout.svelte) is rendered, and render DatabaseSelector next to it. The header should show "Tenant: [dropdown] Database: [dropdown]".

### 7. Drop X-Axon-Database from the codebase

    grep -rn "X-Axon-Database" ui/

Should return zero lines after this bead.

### 8. Tests

bun test in ui/:
- ui/src/lib/api.test.ts (or similar) — if there's an existing test file, extend it. If not, create a small one that:
  - Mocks fetch
  - Calls request("/collections", undefined, { tenant: "acme", database: "orders" })
  - Asserts the mocked fetch was called with "/tenants/acme/databases/orders/collections" (URL-encoded)
  - Verifies no X-Axon-Database header is present

Also:
- npm run check (svelte-check) must pass
- npm run lint must pass if defined

## Out of scope (defer to H2 or follow-ups)

- Credential management UI (that's H2)
- JWT auth flow in the UI (login screen, token storage) — H2 territory
- Deep migration of the legacy /control/tenants to the new schema — post-D3 cleanup
- GraphQL path updates — no GraphQL in the UI currently

## Context

- D3 removed X-Axon-Database from the server REST gateway. Any request still sending it is silently ignored.
- D4 moved GraphQL under the nested path.
- The UI has been running against legacy paths — it must now be path-based or it breaks.
- Svelte 5 runes ($state, $effect, $derived) are the reactive pattern; the existing stores file uses them.

## Files to touch

- ui/src/lib/stores.svelte.ts — add selectedDatabase state + getters/setters
- ui/src/lib/api.ts — rewrite request(), update every export signature, add fetchTenantDatabases + TenantDatabase type
- ui/src/lib/DatabaseSelector.svelte — NEW
- ui/src/routes/+layout.svelte (or wherever the tenant selector lives) — render DatabaseSelector
- ui/src/routes/schemas/+page.svelte — update dbName call sites
- ui/src/routes/audit/+page.svelte — update dbName call sites
- ui/src/routes/collections/+page.svelte — update dbName call sites
- ui/src/routes/collections/[name]/+page.svelte — update dbName call sites
- ui/src/lib/api.test.ts (or wherever tests live) — add scope-building test

## Files NOT to touch

- Any Rust crate — no backend changes
- sdk/typescript — that's G1/G2 territory
- ui/src/routes/tenants/+page.svelte — this page manages tenants via the legacy CRUD; if it needs any change it's just field renames to match API types
- ui/src/routes/*.svelte.test.ts — existing tests stay green (may need scope argument updates)

## Verification

- bun run check (or npm run check) — svelte-check must pass
- bun test (or npm test) — tests must pass
- Manual: ui/ dev server starts without errors; the header shows tenant + database dropdowns; selecting a tenant auto-populates databases; selecting a database re-fetches collections
- grep -rn X-Axon-Database ui/ returns zero lines
